(658, 1, '2014-05-06 13:38:06', '2014-05-06 12:38:06', 'The Hardt Foundation for the Study of Classical Antiquity, in pursuit of its ambition to promote the study of the culture and civilization of Greco-Roman antiquity, offers young researchers an opportunity to apply for research scholarships covering stays of two to four weeks. Applications are not accepted for the months of July and August.\r\n\r\nThe scholarship covers\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the cost of residence at the Hardt Foundation (single room, full board)</li>\r\n	<li>part of the travel expenses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAreas of research supported are Greek and Latin language and literature, ancient history, ancient philosophy and ancient law. The aim of the research stay is the publication of articles, books or other written contributions.\r\n\r\nEligibility\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>up to 35 years of age at the time of application</li>\r\n	<li>PhD candidate (2nd year, at least) or post-doctoral researcher</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nApplicants are requested to submit the following documents:\r\n\r\n-    a curriculum vitæ\r\n-    a cover letter\r\n-    a research proposal\r\n-    two letters of recommendation from university professors\r\n-    a copy or scan of identification (passport or identity card)\r\n-    for applicants who are not university faculty (full, associate or assistant professor), a description of their career plans\r\n\r\nThe documents (in PDF) are to be uploaded on the applicant’s profile via the online registration system. Incomplete applications will not be reviewed.\r\n\r\nThe closing dates for the submission of applications and letters from referees are as follows:\r\n- 30th November for stays requested between early February and late June\r\n- 30th April for stays requested between early September and the end of November.\r\n\r\nDecisions on scholarship will be made in the weeks following the closing dates. All applicants will be notified of the results as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nAt the end of their stay, beneficiaries of scholarships will be required to submit a brief report on their research. They are also requested to mention the support of the Hardt Foundation in any publication arising from work undertaken during their stay.\r\n\r\nThis programme is funded by the Hans Wilsdorf Foundation, Geneva, the Saint-Charles Foundation, Vaduz, and other sponsors.', 'Research scholarships', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '458-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-06 13:38:06', '2014-05-06 12:38:06', '', 458, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=658', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
