(662, 1, '2014-05-06 13:51:22', '2014-05-06 12:51:22', 'The Entretiens sur l’Antiquité classique\r\n\r\n“Each year, at the Foundation’s home in Vandœuvres, the ‘Entretiens sur l’Antiquité Classique’ will be held, during which specialists from all over the world will speak about a chosen field, and in the course of further discussions will engage in enriching exchange of views.” These were Baron Kurd von Hardt’s own words in the introduction to the first volume of the Entretiens, published in 1954 under the title La notion du divin depuis Homère jusqu’à Platon.\r\n\r\nSince 1952, 60 Entretiens have taken place on a variety of topics. The 60 volumes of the proceedings and following discussions offer an overview of classical culture as approached by over 200 scholars.', 'Entretiens', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '396-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-06 13:51:22', '2014-05-06 12:51:22', '', 396, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=662', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(660, 1, '2014-05-06 13:44:31', '2014-05-06 12:44:31', 'The Entretiens sur l’Antiquité classique\r\n\r\n“Each year, at the Foundation’s home in Vandœuvres, the ‘Entretiens sur l’Antiquité Classique’ will be held, during which specialists from all over the world will speak about a chosen field, and in the course of further discussions will engage in enriching exchange of views.” These were Baron Kurd von Hardt’s own words in the introduction to the first volume of the Entretiens, published in 1954 under the title La notion du divin depuis Homère jusqu’à Platon.\r\n\r\nSince 1952, 60 Entretiens have taken place on a variety of topics. The 60 volumes of the proceedings and following discussions offer an overview of classical culture as approached by over 200 scholars.\r\n\r\nNext Entretiens\r\nThe 61st Entretiens sur l''Antiquité classique will take place from August 25 to 29, 2014 on the topic “Cosmologies et cosmogonies dans la littérature antique – Cosmologies and Cosmogonies in Ancient Literature.” These Entretiens are under the direction of Therese Fuhrer and Michael Erler.\r\n\r\nProgramme of the 61st  Entretiens sur l''Antiquité classique.', 'Entretiens', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '396-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-06 13:44:31', '2014-05-06 12:44:31', '', 396, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=660', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
