(934, 1, '2014-05-20 15:15:56', '2014-05-20 13:15:56', '<strong>1950</strong>\r\nInception of the “Hardt Foundation for the Study of Classical Antiquity.”\r\n\r\n<strong>1952  </strong>\r\nThe first Entretiens sur l’Antiquité classique are held.\r\n\r\n<strong>1954 </strong>\r\nThe first volume of the Entretiens is published.\r\n\r\n<strong>1958  </strong>\r\nDeath of Baron Kurd von Hardt. Olivier Reverdin, Professor of the University of Geneva, becomes President of the Foundation.\r\n\r\n<strong>1996</strong>\r\nFrançois Paschoud, Professor of the University of Geneva, President of the Foundation\r\n\r\n<strong>2003    </strong>\r\nMargarethe Billerbeck, Professor of the University of Fribourg, President of the Foundation.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nPierre Ducrey, Honorary Professor of the University of Lausanne, President of the Foundation.\r\n\r\n<strong>2010 </strong>\r\nPascal Couchepin, former federal Counsellor, President of the Foundation; Pierre Ducrey director.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Hardt Foundation in a few figures (2013)</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Guests</strong>\r\nNumber of guests in 2013 : 133\r\nNumber of countries represented : 21\r\n\r\n<strong>Entretiens sur l’Antiquité classique</strong>\r\nEntretiens sur l’Antiquité classique (1952-2013) : 60\r\nVolumes published (as of 2013)<strong> </strong>: 59\r\n\r\n<strong>Conferences and academic events</strong>\r\nNumber of conferences and other academic events hosted in 2013 : 14\r\nOverall number of participants  : 400', 'History of the Foundation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '440-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-20 15:15:56', '2014-05-20 13:15:56', '', 440, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=934', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
