(679, 1, '2014-05-06 14:43:24', '2014-05-06 13:43:24', 'The library of The Hardt Foundation is a highly specialised research library. It provides its guests with the texts and working tools necessary for their research.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>  40,000 volumes</li>\r\n	<li>Approximately 100 specialised journals</li>\r\n	<li>Texts by Greek and Latin authors, from Homer to the Church Fathers, including commentaries, corpora, scholia and indexes</li>\r\n	<li>Greek and Roman history</li>\r\n	<li>Ancient philosophy</li>\r\n	<li>Greek and Roman epigraphy</li>\r\n	<li>Greek and Roman numismatics</li>\r\n	<li>Papyrology</li>\r\n	<li>Archaeology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIntended primarily for the use of our in-house guests, the library may, however, be made available to outside researchers upon request.\r\n\r\nPlease do not hesitate to contact us.', 'The library', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '416-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-06 14:43:24', '2014-05-06 13:43:24', '', 416, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=679', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
