  Should you wish to do further research in the Hardt catalogue, you can either return to this page or stay on the Geneva Library Network website by limiting your search to the Hardt Foundation.\n\n<strong>Tips</strong>\nTruncation\nYou can truncate your search terms by using:\n<ul>\n	<li>an asterisk (*) to replace an indeterminate number of characters</li>\n	<li>a question mark ( ?) to replace a precise number of characters</li>\n</ul>\nExample: V?rgil*  The system searches for Virgile Virgil Virgilio Virgilius Vergil Vergilius...\n\n<strong>Phrases </strong>\nUsing quotation marks (") allows you to search for a phrase, i.e. a series of words in a precise order\nExample: "Commentarii belli Gallici".\n\nFor more informations, please consult <a title="aide en ligne" href="http://help.opac.rero.ch/fr/ge/o/index.html" target="_blank">the help of the Geneva Library Network</a>\n\nUne recherche rapide vous conduira sur le site du Catalogue des bibliothèques genevoises. Une liste de notices bibliographiques apparaîtra à l''écran; pour obtenir la cote d’un document, cliquez sur le numéro de la notice.\n\nSi vous souhaitez faire d''autres recherches dans le catalogue de la Fondation, vous pouvez revenir sur cette page ou continuer sur le site des bibliothèques genevoises en limitant votre recherche, sur la liste déroulante, à la Fondation Hardt.\n\n<strong>Astuces</strong>\n\nTroncature\nVous pouvez tronquer vos termes de recherches en utilisant :\n<ul>\n	<li>un astérisque (*) pour remplacer un nombre indéterminé de caractères</li>\n	<li>un <em>point d''interrogation</em> (?) pour remplacer un nombre précis de caractères.</li>\n</ul>\nExemple: V?rgil*  Le système cherchera Virgile Virgil Virgilio Virgilius Vergil Vergilius...\n\nLocution\nPar l''usage des guillemets, vous pouvez rechercher une suite de mots dans un ordre précis.\nExemple: "Commentarii belli Gallici".\n\nPour plus d''informations, veuillez consulter <a title="aide en ligne" href="http://help.opac.rero.ch/fr/ge/o/index.html" target="_blank">l''aide du réseau des bibliothèques genevoises</a>.', 'Catalogues / search', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '417-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-05-14 21:48:17', '2014-05-14 20:48:17', '', 417, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=825', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(826, 1, '2014-05-14 21:49:07', '2014-05-14 20:49:07', '<strong>Quick search\r\n</strong>You can run a quick search in the library catalogue by typing keywords separated by a space.\r\nExample: Politica Aristoteles\r\n[create_static_search_form]\r\n\r\nA quick search will take you to the Geneva Library Network website. A list of bibliographical references will appear. In order to obtain the call reference, click on the reference number.   Should you wish to do further research in the Hardt catalogue, you can either return to this page or stay on the Geneva Library Network website by limiting your search to the Hardt Foundation.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tips</strong>\r\nTruncation\r\nYou can truncate your search terms by using:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>an asterisk (*) to replace an indeterminate number of characters</li>\r\n	<li>a question mark ( ?) to replace a precise number of characters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nExample: V?rgil*  The system searches for Virgile Virgil Virgilio Virgilius Vergil Vergilius...\r\n\r\n<strong>Phrases </strong>\r\nUsing quotation marks (") allows you to search for a phrase, i.e. a series of words in a precise order\r\nExample: "Commentarii belli Gallici".\r\n\r\nFor more informations, please consult <a title="aide en ligne" href="http://help.opac.rero.ch/fr/ge/o/index.html" target="_blank">the help of the Geneva Library Network</a>.', 'Catalogues / search', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '417-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-14 21:49:07', '2014-05-14 20:49:07', '', 417, 'http://localhost/www_fondationHardt/?p=826', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(827, 1, '2014-05-22 10:42:52', '2014-05-22 08:42:52', 'Thanks to an agreement with the University of Geneva, several electronic resources are accessible from the library of the Hardt Foundation.\n\n<strong>E-journals\n</strong><a title="Revue éléctronique" href="http://resolver.rero.ch/unige/az" target="_blank">The A-Z e-Journals</a> List proposed and maintained by the libraries of the University of Geneva gives access to all e-journals to which this university subscribes.\n\n<strong>Selection of databases</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><a title="JSTOR" href="http://www.jstor.org/" target="_blank">JSTOR</a></li>\n	<li><a title="Année Philologique" href="http://www.annee-philologique.com/" target="_blank">L’Année philologique</a></li>\n	<li><a title="Gnomon" href="http://www.gnomon.ku-eichstaett.de/Gnomon/fr/Gnomon.html" target="_blank">Gnomon on line</a></li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Selection of reference books</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Thesaurus Linguae Graecae</li>\n	<li><a title="Product Information Bibliotheca Teubneriana Latina " href="http://www.degruyter.com/databasecontent;jsessionid=1514FA5E52CE60FA49B018C50485EF05?dbid=btltll&amp;dbsource=%2Fdb%2Fbtltll&amp;col=Coll_BTL-TLL" target="_blank">Bibliotheca Teubneriana Latina</a></li>\n	<li>Library of Latin Texts</li>\n	<li>LLT Series A et LTT Series B</li>\n	<li><a title="Brepolis" href="http://apps.brepolis.net/LTool/Entrance.aspx?w=14&amp;a=%2fdld%2fDefault.aspx" target="_blank">Database of latin Dictionaries</a></li>\n	<li><a title="BrillOnline" href="http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/browse/der-neue-pauly?fromBrillOnline=true" target="_blank">der Neue Pauly</a> and <a title="BrillOnline" href="http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/browse/brill-s-new-pauly?fromBrillOnline=true" target="_blank">Brill''s New Pauly</a></li>\n	<li>Daremberg &amp; Saglio</li>\n</ul>\nTo access other electronic resources, please consult the Register of the databases and reference books. This register includes bibliographical databases, reference b